'''Acracy''' (from [[Greek language|Greek]] α- (no) and κρατία (system of government)) refers to the negation of rule or "government by none". It differs from "[[anarchy]]" as used by [[anarchism|anarchists]] in that it refers solely to absence of political authority, saying nothing of economic authority, whereas anarchy is absence of both.

